<doc id="1075512" wikidata="Q6536231" url="?curid=1075512" title="Lewis (robot)">
<text>Lewis (named after Meriwether Lewis) is an autonomous robot that performs the job of a wedding photographer: it attends social events, moves around, and takes digital photographs of people. It is a research project of the Media and Machines Laboratory at Washington University in St. Louis.

Lewis has been featured on slashdot, on CNN&#x27;s website, and in various North American newspapers.

In 2002, Lewis received -- and declined -- an invitation to Nelly&#x27;s 24th birthday party.
